library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
library(stringr)
library(ggplot2)

# Load the data
data <- read.csv("listings.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Clean the price column by removing non-numeric characters including the dollar sign
data$price <- as.numeric(gsub("[^0-9.]", "", data$price))

# Convert host_is_superhost to numeric binary
data$host_is_superhost <- ifelse(data$host_is_superhost == "t", 1, 0)

# Remove entries with missing values in the key columns
data <- data %>%
  filter(!is.na(price), !is.na(review_scores_rating), !is.na(bedrooms),
         !is.na(host_is_superhost), !is.na(accommodates),
         !is.na(neighbourhood_cleansed), !is.na(property_type),
         !is.na(review_scores_cleanliness), !is.na(review_scores_location),
         !is.na(availability_365))

# Handle outliers in price
Q1 <- quantile(data$price, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE)
Q3 <- quantile(data$price, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE)
IQR <- Q3 - Q1
price_min <- Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
price_max <- Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
data <- data %>%
  filter(price >= price_min & price <= price_max)

# Select and write the cleaned and extended data to a new CSV file
selected_columns <- c(
  "price", "review_scores_rating", "bedrooms", "host_is_superhost", 
  "accommodates", "neighbourhood_cleansed", "room_type",
  "review_scores_cleanliness", "review_scores_location", "availability_365"
)
selected_data <- data[, selected_columns]

summary(selected_data)

# 价格直方图和密度图
ggplot(selected_data, aes(x = price)) + 
  geom_histogram(bins = 30, fill = "blue", color = "black") +  # 直方图
  labs(title = "Price Distribution", x = "Price", y = "Count") 

# 房间类型分布条形图
ggplot(selected_data, aes(x = room_type)) + 
  geom_bar(fill = "black") +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Room Types", x = "Room Type", y = "Count") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

# 不同房间类型的价格箱形图
ggplot(selected_data, aes(x = room_type, y = price)) + 
  geom_boxplot(fill = "green") +
  labs(title = "Price Distribution by Room Type", x = "Room Type", y = "Price") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

  labs(title = "Price vs. Bedrooms")

library(lme4)
lmer_model <- lmer(price ~ review_scores_rating + bedrooms + host_is_superhost + 
                     accommodates + room_type + review_scores_cleanliness + 
                     review_scores_location + availability_365 + 
                     (1 | neighbourhood_cleansed), data = selected_data)
